<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Beard1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Beard,</orth> the hair that grows in the face: <bibl n="shak. luc 1405" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1405</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 1, 9</bibl>. <cit><quote>a great round b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a little yellow b., a Cain-coloured b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 20</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.188" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.76" default="NO" valid="yes">3, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 32</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.834" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 834</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 2, 50</bibl> <cit><quote>your straw-colour b., your orange-tawny b., your purple-in-grain b., or your French-crown-colour b., your perfect yellow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 2, 50</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.99" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.155" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 7, 155</bibl> <cit><quote>(b. of formal cut).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.218" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 218</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.218" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 218</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.218" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 218</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.728" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 728</bibl> <cit><quote>(will make him scratch his b.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 3, 37</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.175" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 175</bibl> etc. etc. <cit><quote>beard to beard,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.10.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 10, 11</bibl></cit> and <bibl n="shak. mac 5.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 5, 6</bibl>. Witches had beards: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.204" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 46</bibl>.<lb />Figuratively the prickles on the ears of corn: <cit><quote>with white and bristly b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 12.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 12, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the green corn hath rotted ere his youth attained a b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 95</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>